JOHANNESBUR - At least three men have been shot dead and fifteen others arrested, during a shooting with Ekurhuleni metro police. The shootout ensued after police received a tip-off, about armed people in the bushes near Angelo Informal settlement in Boksburg. They spotted four men brandishing rifles fitted with telescopes. READ:Â Legislate illegal mining, ANCYL asks Minister of Mineral Resources It's believed the men are tasked with protecting illegal miners. Upon searching the area police arrested fifteen men suspected to be involved in illegal mining. Four rifles with filed-off serial numbers were recovered. The suspects are expected to appear in the Boksburg Magistrate's Court soon. eNCA